title: Grateful Dead Live at Blossom Music Center on 1985-06-25
description:
Set 1

Day Tripper-> West L.A. Fadeaway-> CC Rider, Dire Wolf, Beat It On Down The Line-> Row Jimmy, Me & My Uncle, Big River, Big Railroad Blues, Jack Straw-> Might As Well

Set 2

Gimme Some Lovin'-> China Cat Sunflower-> I Know You Rider-> Playin' In The Band-> Drums-> The Wheel-> Playin' In The Band-> China Doll-> Sugar Magnolia, E: Touch Of Gray

reviews.review_text:
jack straw is funny



energy, fun, the grateful dead

grate! grate grate grate setlist here, what a mix of tunes and all goes together so well with exceptional playing throughout

love the touch as encore

Might As WELL!!! A fun Day Tripper and a FANTASTIC Might as Well sandwich an otherwise average but remarkably long first set. The space jam freaked a lot of us out during a good, but unremarkably second set.  RiverBend the night before was probably better.

High Time had by all So me and my 2 best friend head to Blossom, beautiful place out in the woods, gorgeous day. I was a member of the Belkin Concert Club but wasnt sure where our seats where.  We get there right before show time, I remember heading to our seats, and the ushers kept waving us forward, ever forward.  Ended up 4th row dead center , took a quik look around in amazement, just then the lights go down.  "Day Tripper" and the place goes nuts.  What a great time and place to be a deadhead!
Awesome Blossom My all time favorite Sugar Mag.

It took so long to find out--but I found out Checking out shows just out of reach in 85.
This first set is blazing!!! 
standard set list (Besides Daytripper)
